summary: An ordinance providing for the execution and acceptance of an agreement between the Northern Pacific Railway Company and The City of Seattle for the extension of the right to establish a temporary road crossing over and across the right-of-way of said railway company in the northeast quarter of the southwest quarter of Section 9, Township 25 North, Range 4 East, W. M., entered into pursuant to Ordinance No. 59380, approved May 13, 1930.
